comment.text: Fatty acid synthetase catalyzes the formation of long-chain fatty acids from acetyl-CoA, malonyl-CoA and NADPH. This multifunctional protein has 7 catalytic activities and an acyl carrier protein.
Acetyl-CoA + n malonyl-CoA + 2n NADPH = a long-chain fatty acid + (n+1) CoA + n CO(2) + 2n NADP(+).
A (3R)-3-hydroxyacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] = a trans-2-enoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + H(2)O.
An acyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADP(+) = a trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-[acyl-carrier protein] + NADPH.

Homodimer which is arranged in a head to tail fashion (PubMed:17618296, PubMed:18022563, Ref.27). Interacts with CEACAM1; this interaction is insulin and phosphorylation-dependent; reduces fatty-acid synthase activity (By similarity).
Identified by mass spectrometry in melanosome fractions from stage I to stage IV.
Ubiquitous. Prominent expression in brain, lung, and liver.
The relatively low beta-ketoacyl synthase activity may be attributable to the low 4'-phosphopantetheine content of the protein.
